  "original_title": "45  \u0bb5\u0bc0\u0ba4\u0bae\u0bbe\u0ba9 \u0bb9\u0bc7\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bc1\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bc0\u0bb0\u0bc6\u0ba9 \u0b87\u0bb0\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0ba9\u0bae\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b86\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc7 \u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0ba3\u0bae\u0bcd - \u0b9a\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0bb2\u0bbe \u0b85\u0baa\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf \u0b85\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb0 \u0b9a\u0baa\u0bc8",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "45% of hotel bookings suddenly canceled due to protests - Tourism Development Authority",
      "author": "Digital Desk 5",
      "body_lines": [
        "Sri Lanka Tourism Development Authority Chairman Tammika Wijesinghe said that 45 percent of hotel reservations made by foreign tourists to come to Sri Lanka have been suddenly canceled due to the recent protests and demonstrations in the country.",
        "Such issues have had a very negative impact on the tourism sector. Apart from this, shortage of fuel and gas and power cuts are other major factors for the decline in tourist arrivals.",
        "Tourist arrivals have increased by 10 percent in the period so far this month, with 42,925 tourists visiting so far this month. Normally, the average number of tourists on a weekday is 1533. He further noted that the average number on weekends is 1900.",
        "August is usually the peak tourist season in Sri Lanka. Therefore, a special program has been started to attract more tourists to the country during this period.",
        "Tammika Wijesinghe, the chairperson of the Sri Lanka Tourism Development Authority, mentioned that a tourism promotion program has been started targeting Kandy Perahara to attract tourists and steps have been taken to provide various facilities including providing fuel for the transportation of tourists."
      ],
